Question: Store parts of string in a string array: :I have a string  tajmahal.txt sarjan.pdf noorjahan.exe. I want to store this string in a string array such that ar[0] = tajmahal.txt, ar[1] = sarjan.pdf and ar[2] = noorjahan.exe. How can I do it without using any build functions in java (because I am using j2me which does not support many j2se functions). Any help would be great. Thanks in advance.
Please using this api: StringTokenizer.nextToken.
Answer:
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(str, ".");
String[] ar = new String[st.countTokens()];
int i = 0;
while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
    ar[i] = st.nextToken();
    i++;
}

Explanation:
StringTokenizer is a class in java.util package. It is used to break a string into tokens. It takes two arguments, the string to be broken and the delimiter. The delimiter is the character or string that separates the tokens. In this case, the delimiter is ".".
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(str, ".");
This line creates a new StringTokenizer object and initializes it with the string to be broken and the delimiter.
String[] ar = new String[st.countTokens()];
This line creates a new string array and initializes it with the number of tokens in the string.
int i = 0;
This line creates a new integer variable and initializes it with 0.
while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
    ar[i] = st.nextToken();
    i++;
}
This line is a while loop that continues until there are no more tokens in the string. It stores the next token in the string array and increments the integer variable.

